00:07:21.300 --> 00:07:24.620
But in order to build
something really engaging,

00:07:24.620 --> 00:07:27.430
something that really stands
out on the Android platform

00:07:27.430 --> 00:07:30.500
or fits cohesively
within the system,

00:07:30.500 --> 00:07:32.450
you're going to need
to understand material

00:07:32.450 --> 00:07:34.867
extremely well.

00:07:34.867 --> 00:07:36.283
And what parts of
material are you

00:07:36.283 --> 00:07:38.544
going to need to
understand for Sketch?

00:07:38.544 --> 00:07:40.210
Not as much of the
motion, although it's

00:07:40.210 --> 00:07:43.640
important for
developing a great app.

00:07:43.640 --> 00:07:47.671
You will need to understand
the colors and the typography

00:07:47.671 --> 00:07:49.170
and just basically
everything that's

00:07:49.170 --> 00:07:51.170
going to be on the
static screen very well.

00:07:53.850 --> 00:07:56.490
So the first topic that is going
to be really important when

00:07:56.490 --> 00:07:58.350
you're going to
start a design is

00:07:58.350 --> 00:08:01.190
going to be what colors
you're going to use.

00:08:01.190 --> 00:08:05.600
So the spec says that you need
to use bold hues juxtaposed

00:08:05.600 --> 00:08:09.470
with muted environments, deep
shadows, bright highlights.

00:08:09.470 --> 00:08:12.120
And what that comes
down to is you'll

00:08:12.120 --> 00:08:14.140
have a bunch of
different colors,

00:08:14.140 --> 00:08:17.350
so you'll open up all
the color palettes.

00:08:17.350 --> 00:08:20.950
This is indigo here
with a pink accent.

00:08:20.950 --> 00:08:25.410
And you'll want to
pick three main colors

00:08:25.410 --> 00:08:28.140
from the main
palette, and you'll

00:08:28.140 --> 00:08:30.880
want to pick one color
from an accent palette.

00:08:30.880 --> 00:08:35.610
And what I like to do
is just-- I'm sorry.

00:08:35.610 --> 00:08:36.490
All right.

00:08:36.490 --> 00:08:37.809
I thought there was a question.

00:08:37.809 --> 00:08:41.370
But what I like
to do is just try

00:08:41.370 --> 00:08:44.530
to get a feel for what
kind of app I'm making.

00:08:44.530 --> 00:08:45.710
Is it serious?

00:08:45.710 --> 00:08:46.705
Is it more playful?

00:08:46.705 --> 00:08:49.080
If it's more playful, I'll
probably use a brighter color.

00:08:49.080 --> 00:08:52.570
If it's more serious or the
content really shines out,

00:08:52.570 --> 00:08:55.380
I'll probably use
a more muted color.

00:08:55.380 --> 00:08:59.780
But a bold color on
a muted environment--

00:08:59.780 --> 00:09:01.780
pick three colors,
and just play around

00:09:01.780 --> 00:09:04.126
with which colors you pick.

00:09:04.126 --> 00:09:06.250
Typography is very important
and the color that you

00:09:06.250 --> 00:09:07.890
pick on your typography.

00:09:07.890 --> 00:09:09.950
The spec lays this
out very clearly.

00:09:09.950 --> 00:09:14.470
If it's a light background,
you want to pick a darker text.

00:09:14.470 --> 00:09:17.090
If it's a dark background,
you pick a lighter text.

00:09:17.090 --> 00:09:19.090
If it's emphasized,
you don't want

00:09:19.090 --> 00:09:20.930
to put any transparency
on the text.

00:09:20.930 --> 00:09:24.190
If it is just kind of like
a subtitle or something,

00:09:24.190 --> 00:09:28.510
you might want to put a little
transparency on the text.

00:09:28.510 --> 00:09:33.040
Imagery-- so imagery is
obviously very important.

00:09:33.040 --> 00:09:35.970
It's a powerful tool to help you
communicate and differentiate

00:09:35.970 --> 00:09:37.150
your product.

00:09:37.150 --> 00:09:39.780
You want to use bold graphics.

00:09:39.780 --> 00:09:43.040
Intentional imagery
helps to engage a user.

00:09:43.040 --> 00:09:44.830
Apps that have a bunch
of images in them--

00:09:44.830 --> 00:09:47.620
you want to use them more.

00:09:47.620 --> 00:09:51.940
So you want to be very
intentional with what kind

00:09:51.940 --> 00:09:54.130
of images you choose.

00:09:54.130 --> 00:09:55.790
And you want to
choose ones that are

00:09:55.790 --> 00:09:57.850
contextual to your experience.

00:09:57.850 --> 00:10:00.660
If you have a
travel app, you want

00:10:00.660 --> 00:10:03.480
to show pictures of your
actual destination city

00:10:03.480 --> 00:10:06.952
if you're showing like
a plane ride or whatnot.

00:10:06.952 --> 00:10:08.410
If you're showing
user information,

00:10:08.410 --> 00:10:11.000
try to show a picture
of that actual user

00:10:11.000 --> 00:10:16.760
instead of just like
a random person.

00:10:16.760 --> 00:10:19.110
That seems contrived,
but you can always

00:10:19.110 --> 00:10:22.080
kind of think contextually, what
kind of images can I show here?

00:10:22.080 --> 00:10:23.360
What can I not?

00:10:23.360 --> 00:10:25.500
And there's a lot of
rules around images

00:10:25.500 --> 00:10:28.090
in material design.

00:10:28.090 --> 00:10:32.120
You can use multiple
mediums, so if you

00:10:32.120 --> 00:10:34.310
don't have a bunch of
actual photography,

00:10:34.310 --> 00:10:39.460
it's OK to mix in
artwork and drawings.

00:10:39.460 --> 00:10:41.870
So if you've got
a profile picture,

00:10:41.870 --> 00:10:45.020
you don't have to just use
a picture of that person.

00:10:45.020 --> 00:10:47.800
If you don't have it,
it's OK to mix it and show

00:10:47.800 --> 00:10:50.770
a drawing of the person.

00:10:50.770 --> 00:10:55.630
But just really contextual to
your experience, immersive.

00:10:55.630 --> 00:10:58.230
If it's a big hero image,
have it bleed all the way

00:10:58.230 --> 00:11:00.580
to the edge and
things like that.

00:11:00.580 --> 00:11:03.820
So you can really
humanize an app

00:11:03.820 --> 00:11:07.580
by the imagery that's in it.

00:11:07.580 --> 00:11:11.940
And typography-- typography
is just such a huge topic,

00:11:11.940 --> 00:11:16.820
so it's really hard to go
over everything right now.

00:11:16.820 --> 00:11:21.102
But just know the fonts
that you want to use,

00:11:21.102 --> 00:11:23.310
generally, it's going to be
Roboto, Noto, because you

00:11:23.310 --> 00:11:24.685
get those for
free, and you don't

00:11:24.685 --> 00:11:27.269
have to get licenses for them.

00:11:27.269 --> 00:11:28.310
They match on the system.

00:11:28.310 --> 00:11:30.740
They're optimized
for the system,

00:11:30.740 --> 00:11:34.860
so they'll be able to render
them the fastest and whatnot.

00:11:34.860 --> 00:11:42.710
But just make sure to
use that and kind of look

00:11:42.710 --> 00:11:46.285
over the typography spec
and learn a little bit

00:11:46.285 --> 00:11:47.285
about what you're doing.

